Conscience (Noun) Vs. Conscious (Adj.) Vs. Conscientious (Adj.)

Meaning- Conscience refers to the awareness of one's morality (as in what is right or wrong).
                - Conscious refers to being awake or alert.
                - Conscientious refers to a person who does things correctly and carefully.

Example- I advised my students to let their conscience guide them.
               - When he fell, he hit his head hard but luckily he remained conscious.
               -  Shikha was a conscientious student and graduated at the top of her class.
